<item>
            <title>[HBASE-735] hbase shell doesn&apos;t trap CTRL-C signal</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-735</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;From withing the hbase shell, when there&apos;s a IO problem, the hbase client code tries to recover automatically but sometimes we know what&apos;s going on and all we want is to cancel the operation by pressing CTRL-C but the shell doesn&apos;t catch it and we need to either wait for the operation to timeout or close the terminal and open another one.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12399972">HBASE-735</key>
            <summary>hbase shell doesn&apos;t trap CTRL-C signal</summary>
