                            <comment id="12612576" author="jdcryans" created="Thu, 10 Jul 2008 17:10:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1. An easy way of getting an IO error is shutting down HBase and trying almost anything in the shell.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12612580" author="jdcryans" created="Thu, 10 Jul 2008 17:23:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Removed the sigint trap in hirb&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12612585" author="stack" created="Thu, 10 Jul 2008 17:40:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.  Thanks for the patch J-D. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is improves over what was there previous but kills the shell altogether.  Best would be our killing the outstanding process if we could leaving the shell up.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
